limerick_list.text:
Don't confuse the word bromate with brumate;
One's an ion and here is your clue, mate:
It has brom- (comes from bromine;
I'm sorry I'm so mean);
The other's what snakes sometimes do, mate.

Amazing, that name Amaziah:
A Levite, the son of Hilkiah;
A king that was famous;
A priest (just see Amos);
And a subject of King Hezekiah!

With no backbone, you cannot stand straight;
It supports your entire body's weight.
It's a vertebral tower
That is curved, but has power;
All those bones make a spine that's first-rate!

Far removed both in time and in space,
In connection, and one's mental place;
Likeness slight, hard to see;
And aloof.  We agree
That that's distant, so need we retrace?

With my spanking new shake axe, or froe,
Split off shingles, planks, kindling like so:
Set the blade with the grain;
Thwack again and again;
Rock the haft back and forth. You're a pro!

How they loved it, those pirates of old;
When they supped it, it helped them feel bold;
Made of sugar and rum,
They thought bumbo was yum—
As they buried their woes and their gold.

Yellow star-shaped florets gently sway;
Atop slim, fern-like stalks they sashay.
Strange that Bambi steers clear;
Even hares won't come near.
Coreopsis is tops, hip hooray.

We've quite a variety of rice;
For paella, bahia is nice.
It's Spanish, short-grains;
In the mouth it remains—
And when rice is so scrumptious, chew twice.

So you thought writing lims was a snap?
You've begun every line with a cap;
There's impeccable rhyme;
And your meter's sublime.
But here's news for ya buddy: it's crap!

It's a desert for Sandgropers (strewth!);
A guitar Zappa played (in my youth);
Or a braveheart called Mel
(Now that must ring a bell!);
Or a cocktail of gin and vermouth.

Peanut brickle is causing a stickle;
This snack has us caught in a pickle.
The candy's too tough;
What can break through this stuff?
Not our molars, but maybe a brick'll.

In the hierarchy, I'm a gesith;
I'm a courtly companion, beneath
Just his lordship, the king,
But that's not a big thing;
I'm a regular guy. Call me Keith.

My ulna, a subject, the core,
Or a die that I toss on the floor;
An ivory bar
That makes rhythm the star;
And a color: All bones I adore!

A fiber that's toxic to man;
A substance we're starting to ban;
A mineral mined.
And now I've defined
Asbestos as best as I can.

Your estate is palatial and grand;
It has gardens and room to expand.
You have plenty of stuff
(Even more than enough);
You are acred:  a man who's got land.

To go off means 'to start down the road';
'Stop; deteriorate; smell'; or 'explode';
Or (relationship-wise)
The bored look in her eyes
And the break-up their message forebode.

On an armrest he's mounted a gun;
In the cushions are tasers that stun.
At the back are the jets;
It's as good as it gets
When your son thinks an armchair is fun!

Hey, the Boxing Day sale is now here;
Grab your coat, get your self into gear!
All the gift wrap's on cheap;
We should buy a whole heap—
And the savings we'll spend on some beer.

Bicoastal means east coast and west coast;
I can't say which one's the best-dressed coast.
They both have that thing
Known as funk, kitsch, or bling;
So wherever I am is the best coast.

I have no dark sin to confess;
Of marriages, I've made no mess;
An adulteress I'm not,
But I flatter a lot:
Adulatress, yes, that I'd profess.

I love dwarsliggers: very small books
One can carry in all kinds of nooks;
Made of paper as thin
As an onion's slim skin;
Cell-phone sized, well-designed, with good looks.

The production was lacking in zest;
With the acting, I wasn't impressed;
The music and lighting
Were both unexciting.
"Amateurishness" sums it up best.
